{0 Diagnostics}

Report unresolved links as diagnostics so the user can distinguish
resolved from unresolved links without navigating.

{1 Trigger}

Diagnostics are published via [textDocument/publishDiagnostics] after
every index rebuild (i.e. on {b didOpen} and {b didSave}, matching
the current rebuild cadence).

{1 Scope}

Every recognized link form in the document is checked:

{ul
  {- {b Wikilinks}: [[[target]]], [[[target#heading]]],
     [[[target#^blockid]]], [![[embed]]]}
  {- {b Markdown links}: [[text](target)]}
  {- {b Markdown images}: [![alt](img.png)]}
}

External URLs ([https://...], [http://...]) are skipped.

{1:resolution_check Resolution check}

Each link is resolved against the vault index via
{!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve}.  A link is {e unresolved} when:

{ul
  {- The target note does not exist in the index.}
  {- A heading fragment ([#heading]) does not match any heading in the
     target file (slugified comparison).}
  {- A block-ID fragment ([#^blockid]) does not match any block in the
     target file.}
}

{1 Diagnostic shape}

{t
  | Field        | Value                                               |
  |--------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
  | range        | byte range of the link (see {!page-"feature-utf16-positions"}) |
  | severity     | Warning                                             |
  | source       | ["oystermark"]                                      |
  | message      | human-readable description, e.g. ["unresolved link: note"] |
}

Resolved links produce no diagnostic.

{1 Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Empty document}: zero diagnostics.}
  {- {b Self-referencing fragment} ([[[#heading]]]): resolved against
     the current file; unresolved if heading/block not found.}
  {- {b Embed links} ([![[note]]]): treated identically to regular
     wikilinks for diagnostic purposes.}
}
